OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1774199468
OL,3,CSunderland take the spoils as Tyne-
OL,4,CWear derby returns after 10 year
OL,5,Cabsence
OL,7,FThere was late derby day dismay for
OL,8,FNewcastle as Sunderland took the
OL,9,Fspoils in the first Tyne-Wear at St
OL,10,FJames' Park in a decade.
OL,12,FNewcastle United were out for revenge
OL,13,Fafter a 1-0 defeat in the reverse
OL,14,Ffixture at the Stadium of Light in
OL,15,FDecember, but a late Brian Brobbey
OL,16,Fstrike meant the Black Cats did the
OL,17,Fdouble over their rivals on Tyneside.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G1/5
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,423,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1774199468
OL,3,CSunderland take the spoils as Tyne-
OL,4,CWear derby returns after 10 year
OL,5,Cabsence
OL,7,FAhead of the game, Eddie Howe told his
OL,8,Fside they must "play like their lives
OL,9,Fdepend on it" and they started on the
OL,10,Ffront foot looking to end a run of 10
OL,11,Fconsecutive league derbies without a
OL,12,Fwin.
OL,14,FAnthony Gordon opened the scoring for
OL,15,Fthe home side, capitalising on a
OL,16,Fmistake by Luke O'Nien in the
OL,17,FSunderland defence to put the Magpies
OL,18,Fahead 10 minutes in.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/5
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,423,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1774199468
OL,3,CSunderland take the spoils as Tyne-
OL,4,CWear derby returns after 10 year
OL,5,Cabsence
OL,7,FShortly before half-time, Sven Botman
OL,8,Fmissed the chance to double the lead
OL,9,Fas his header hit Melke Elberg's post.
OL,11,FThe Black Cats responded in the second
OL,12,Fhalf, as Chamsdine Talbi ushered a
OL,13,Fcorner into the Newcastle net 10
OL,14,Fminutes after the break to pull level.
OL,16,FSunderland Captain Granit Xhaka almost
OL,17,Fgave the visitors the lead as his
OL,18,Fdipping effort looped off the head of
OL,19,FJacob Ramsey and floated narrowly over
OL,20,Fthe bar.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/5
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,423,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1774199468
OL,3,CSunderland take the spoils as Tyne-
OL,4,CWear derby returns after 10 year
OL,5,Cabsence
OL,7,FNewcastle United substitute Malick
OL,8,FThiaw had the ball in the net, but the
OL,9,Fgoal was scrubbe off after Jacob
OL,10,FMurphy was ruled offside.
OL,12,FBut Brian Brobbey struck late to give
OL,13,FSunderland the win, their eleventh
OL,14,Fconsecutive league game against
OL,15,FNewcastle without a defeat and
OL,16,Fextending a period of ten years
OL,17,Fwithout a win for Newcastle.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/5
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
